cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with extracting tree structures from image data using graph-based representations and graph refinement techniques. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. The use of mean-field approximation and graph neural networks are also popular techniques in these fields. Additionally, the paper involves graph theory (cs.GR) and neural networks (cs.NE) which are relevant sub-categories.
